CatDescriptText: Mrs. Almeter Moore, 1345 Grotto Street, 12th Ward, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 31, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Who is your ward chairman? Does he have any power?  Does he exert it?" answer reads: "I don't know the ward chairman mainly because we have been in this ward for only five months.  But I think that whoever he is, he's doing a good job looking out for the welfare of residents because everything is pretty nice."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Almeter Moore wearing dark skirt and light colored cardigan sweater, holding packages outside of store advertising "School Days Specials" and "Back to School Needs"
